The paper focuses on constructing a virtual dataset for traffic vision research using computer graphics, virtual reality, and rule modeling technologies. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of Unity3D platform for rendering and generating accurate ground-truth labels suggests that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on generating photorealistic virtual datasets with high accuracy labeling suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
